CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1778674272
OL,3,CForced adoption scandal: 'I wasn't
OL,4,Cadopted because I was not white'
OL,6,FIn 1962, June Thoburn was a childcare
OL,7,Fofficer in Oxford City, and later in
OL,8,FLondon.
OL,10,FShe was not involved in the running of
OL,11,Fmother and baby institutions, but part
OL,12,Fof her job was to collect babies and
OL,13,Fplace them into care or take them for
OL,14,Fadoption.
OL,16,FShe recalls that the young, single
OL,17,Fmothers had very few options, and that
OL,18,Fthere was inherent prejudice within
OL,19,Fthe adoption system.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/26
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1778674272
OL,3,CForced adoption scandal: 'I wasn't
OL,4,Cadopted because I was not white'
OL,6,F"The assumption was that Black
OL,7,Fchildren could not be adopted," she
OL,8,Ftold ITV News.
OL,10,F"The white babies were placed for
OL,11,Fadoption, the mixed heritage child
OL,12,Fwould almost certainly go into care,
OL,13,Fusually a residential nursery."
OL,15,FShe recalls how when some nursery
OL,16,Fstaff considered if a child could be
OL,17,Fplaced for adoption, they "looked at
OL,18,Fthe fingers nails" to see if they
OL,19,Fcould "pass for white".
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/26
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30610
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1778674272
OL,3,CForced adoption scandal: 'I wasn't
OL,4,Cadopted because I was not white'
OL,6,F"Some of the mixed heritage children
OL,7,Fwere brought up as white," she said.
OL,9,F"We never looked for Black foster
OL,10,Fparents or adopters. It was not until
OL,11,Fthe late 1970's that we even had Black
OL,12,Fsocial workers, most were white and
OL,13,Fmiddle class, like me.
OL,15,F"I was unhappy with the suffering I
OL,16,Fsaw. I'm sad to say I was part of that
OL,17,Fsociety. I was an employee," she added.
OL,19,FIf you have a story to share, contact
OL,20,Fthe social affairs team by emailing:
OL,21,Fsocialaffairs@itv.com
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@ZO]qD@AOUwD@AOUyD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/26
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30611
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1778674272
OL,3,CForced adoption scandal: 'I wasn't
OL,4,Cadopted because I was not white'
OL,6,FIt wasn't until the The Children's Act
OL,7,Fin 1989 required local authorities to
OL,8,F"have regard to the different racial
OL,9,Fgroups to which children within their
OL,10,Farea who are in need belong" and to
OL,11,Fensure that the cultural needs of
OL,12,Fchildren from different ethnic groups
OL,13,Fare met when they are in care.
OL,15,FOur long running ITV news
OL,16,Finvestigation has gathered shocking
OL,17,Ftestimony from across Britain
OL,18,Frevealing layer upon layer of cruelty.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/26
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30612
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1778674272
OL,3,CForced adoption scandal: 'I wasn't
OL,4,Cadopted because I was not white'
OL,6,FSingle mothers were often told that
OL,7,Fthey would be "selfish" to keep their
OL,8,Fbabies and that the infants would have
OL,9,Fbetter lives once they were adopted by
OL,10,Ftwo parent families. The reality was
OL,11,Foften far different.
OL,13,F'You carry that stigma for the rest of
OL,14,Fyour life'
OL,16,FMargaret Moore spent the first three
OL,17,Fyears of her life in an orphanage and
OL,18,Fthen foster care. She believes she was
OL,19,Fnever even considered for adoption
OL,20,Fbecause of her heritage.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/26
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30613
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1778674272
OL,3,CForced adoption scandal: 'I wasn't
OL,4,Cadopted because I was not white'
OL,6,FMs Moore was born at St Pelagia's
OL,7,Fmaternity home in London the 1950s,
OL,8,Fwhich was run by Catholic nuns from
OL,9,Fthe Sisters of the Sacred Heart of
OL,10,FJesus and Mary. She recounted her own
OL,11,F"bleak" start to life.
OL,13,FShe told ITV News: "On my medical
OL,14,Frecords one of the things that really
OL,15,Fhurt me was that they said 'it can
OL,16,Fhear'.
OL,26,@uD@TOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/26
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30614
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1778674272
OL,3,CForced adoption scandal: 'I wasn't
OL,4,Cadopted because I was not white'
OL,6,F"I was considered coloured, that was
OL,7,Fthe phrase then, biracial now. So my
OL,8,Frace was commented on and I think in
OL,9,Fthe homes there was a tier system and
OL,10,FI wasn't considered 'correct for
OL,11,Fadoption'.
OL,13,F"I say I carry a hole in my soul with
OL,14,Fit. You're marked. You carry that
OL,15,Fstigma, you carry it for the rest of
OL,16,Fyour life and the repercussions of
OL,17,Fit," she added.
OL,26,@uD@AOUyD@DO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/26
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30615
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1778674272
OL,3,CForced adoption scandal: 'I wasn't
OL,4,Cadopted because I was not white'
OL,6,FWhile those who were adopted were
OL,7,Foften placed with white families in
OL,8,Fwhite areas of England, feeling
OL,9,Fdisconnected from their own heritage.
OL,11,F'I was thought of as a problem'
OL,13,FCarmen Curran was also born in a home
OL,14,Ffor unmarried mothers in Cumbria in
OL,15,F1961 and placed in an orphanage at 12
OL,16,Fdays old.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/26
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30616
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1778674272
OL,3,CForced adoption scandal: 'I wasn't
OL,4,Cadopted because I was not white'
OL,6,FShe told ITV News that she has seen
OL,7,F"correspondence between the priests
OL,8,Fthat confirms they knew my mother
OL,9,Fthought I would be adopted almost
OL,10,Fimmediately", but her adoption files
OL,11,Fstate "you probably know that the
OL,12,Fchild is very dark and the chances of
OL,13,Fadoption are almost negligible".
OL,15,F"It shows I was thought of as a
OL,16,Fproblem, and they knew that I would
OL,17,Fvery likely spend a long long time in
OL,18,Fan institution," she added.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/26
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30617
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1778674272
OL,3,CForced adoption scandal: 'I wasn't
OL,4,Cadopted because I was not white'
OL,6,FShe was two-years-old when she was
OL,7,Fadopted. Although she had loving
OL,8,Fadoptive parents, questions over her
OL,9,Fidentity always loomed large as she
OL,10,Fgrew up in a white working class
OL,11,Fcommunity in the north east of England.
OL,13,FITV News analysis of government
OL,14,Farchives, newspaper clippings and
OL,15,Facademic journals from the 1960s shows
OL,16,Fracism was widespread throughout the
OL,17,Fadoption system in thew 1950s, 60s and
OL,18,F70s.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/26
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30618
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1778674272
OL,3,CForced adoption scandal: 'I wasn't
OL,4,Cadopted because I was not white'
OL,6,FIn the Journal of Race and Group
OL,7,FRelations academics discuss "the
OL,8,Fimprobability of adoption for non-
OL,9,Fwhite children" in 1968, concluding
OL,10,F"it presents a fairly serious problem
OL,11,Fin a few areas".
OL,13,FWhile newspaper articles from Home
OL,14,FOffice archives from the 1960s and 70s
OL,15,Fdetail how children were not placed
OL,16,Ffor adoptions "because their skins
OL,17,Flook different", describing the babies
OL,18,Fas the "new faces in the children's
OL,19,Fhomes of Britain - the faces which
OL,20,Fdon't fit outside".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/26
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30619
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1778674272
OL,3,CForced adoption scandal: 'I wasn't
OL,4,Cadopted because I was not white'
OL,6,FAn article in the Times newspaper in
OL,7,F1968 states that "some reasons for the
OL,8,Freluctance to adopt are familiar
OL,9,Fenough ... fear of what the neighbours
OL,10,Fwill think looms large".
OL,12,FIn another journal academics commented
OL,13,Fon "adjustment" issues for those who
OL,14,Fwere placed with families.
OL,16,F"A little girl comparing the colour of
OL,17,Fher skin with that of her adoptive
OL,18,Fparents was found trying to scrub her
OL,19,Fhands and arms white with soap
OL,20,Fpowder," it noted.
OL,26,@xD@AOU|D@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/26
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30620
SC,0020
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1778674272
OL,3,CForced adoption scandal: 'I wasn't
OL,4,Cadopted because I was not white'
OL,6,FThere is now growing pressure for the
OL,7,Fchurch and the state, who played
OL,8,Fcentral roles in these cruel practices
OL,9,Fto officially apologise and support
OL,10,Fthose who continue to suffer,
OL,11,Fincluding those who "experienced
OL,12,Fracism at every turn".
OL,14,FIn March the Prime Minister Sir Keir
OL,15,FStarmer told ITV News that his
OL,16,F"instinct" is to issue a government
OL,17,Fapology for the state's role in the
OL,18,Fforced adoption scandal, but no
OL,19,Ftimescale has been set for that
OL,20,Fapology.
