OL,3,CForced adoption scandal: 'I wasn't
OL,4,Cadopted because I was not white'
OL,6,FResponding to this report, a
OL,7,Fgovernment spokesperson said: "This
OL,8,Fabhorrent practice should never have
OL,9,Ftaken place, and our deepest
OL,10,Fsympathies are with all those affected.
OL,12,F"Racism of any kind has no place in
OL,13,Four society and it is deeply
OL,14,Fdisturbing that it played a part in
OL,15,Fthese appalling cases.
OL,17,F"We take the issue of historic forced
OL,18,Fadoptions extremely seriously and
OL,19,Fcontinue to engage with those affected
OL,20,Fto provide support."
OL,26,@oD@_OU|D@TO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G21/26
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30622
SC,0022
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1778674272
OL,3,CForced adoption scandal: 'I wasn't
OL,4,Cadopted because I was not white'
OL,6,FThe Church of England operated and
OL,7,Ffunded 107 mother and baby homes,
OL,8,Fincluding Rosemundy in Cornwall, where
OL,9,FDr Phil Frampton was born, and had
OL,10,Fover 30 adoption agencies.
OL,12,FA Church of England spokesperson said:
OL,13,F"Any instance of racism is abhorrent
OL,14,Fand has no place in the life of the
OL,15,FChurch and we condemn it
OL,16,Funequivocally. These accounts are
OL,17,Fdeeply distressing and sobering.
OL,26,@uD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G22/26
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30623
SC,0023
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1778674272
OL,3,CForced adoption scandal: 'I wasn't
OL,4,Cadopted because I was not white'
OL,6,F"We know that many people experienced
OL,7,Fdeep harm in connection with
OL,8,Fhistorical adoption practices,
OL,9,Fincluding within some mother and baby
OL,10,Fhomes linked to the Church of England.
OL,12,F"This is a cause for great regret and
OL,13,Fsorrow. The Church of England is
OL,14,Fengaged in work to understand its
OL,15,Fhistory, including the pain and trauma
OL,16,Fthis has caused, and to address the
OL,17,Fimpact it continues to have on
OL,18,Fpeople's lives.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G23/26
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30624
SC,0024
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1778674272
OL,3,CForced adoption scandal: 'I wasn't
OL,4,Cadopted because I was not white'
OL,6,F"These events took place in a period
OL,7,Fwhen harmful and prejudicial societal
OL,8,Fattitudes often went unchallenged, and
OL,9,Fthe Church of England was part of that
OL,10,Fcontext and contributed to those
OL,11,Fattitudes. We recognise the harm this
OL,12,Fcaused."
OL,14,FIn 2016 the head of the Catholic
OL,15,FChurch in England and Wales apologised
OL,16,F"for the hurt caused by agencies
OL,17,Facting in the name of the Catholic
OL,18,FChurch".
OL,26,@nD@AOUxD@AOUzD@GO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G24/26
